UID:KDIG2695181322
DTSTART:20260420T220000Z
SEQUENCE:0
TRANSP:OPAQUE
DTEND:20260421T010000Z
LOCATION:4157 Girard Ave
SUMMARY:Girarden Art Build
CLASS:PUBLIC
DESCRIPTION:Make your mark on #MumiaWeek with our Innocence & Abolition Art
  & Crafts Night\, from 6pm to 9pm at the Girarden Wellness Garden\, locate
 d at 4157 West Girard Ave\, Philadelphia. The Girarden Wellness Garden has
  been dealing with some shady land developers that want to steal the space
  away from the community\, so what better way to live our Mumia's politics
  than to occupy that plot and give it back to the people!\n\nAt this art b
 uild\, expert memory workers Lunise Cerin & Wynn Eakins will guide us thro
 ugh a presentation on innocence and revolution in Philadelphia history & n
 ature as we center our revolutionary softness\, re-imagine innocence throu
 gh art and come together for an inspiring garden party under the stars\, c
 reating banners\, signs and other materials to take with us into the March
  of Innocence on Saturday\, April 25th.
CATEGORIES:B.O.O.T.S.
DTSTAMP:20260412T120032Z
CREATED:20260407T021412Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260407T122714Z
END:VEVENT
